The paper deals with a stochastic system and investigates the benefit of predictive scheduling in improving timely-throughput. This involves the use of learning and prediction in network control. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SY (Systems and Control), which deals with the analysis, design, and control of complex systems. The paper also involves communication systems, which suggests the category cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The use of optimization techniques and decision-making processes suggests the category cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also involves the use of machine learning and prediction models, which suggests the category cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper involves the use of algorithms to improve system performance, which suggests the category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
